widgets_values:
Adjusting the ratio of the output blocks 0 to 4 of the model can be used to make it more faithful to the original model.

Note that these values work like:

model1 * ratio + model2 * (1.0 - ratio)
The sigma_min and sigma_max values here are saved in the checkpoint so you should try adjusting them.
A good starting point is the sampling settings of the base model but you might have to adjust them for optimal results.

(cosxl - sdxl) + other_checkpoint
